'''Verity Long-Droppert''' is an Australian softball third base man and outfielder. She attended the University of Western Australia. She has held softball scholarships from the [[Australian Institute of Sport]] and the [[Western Australia Institute of Sport]]. She has represented Australia on the junior and senior levels, and won a bronze medal at the 2007 ISF Junior Women's World Championships.  She played professional softball for Baseball Softball Club Legnano.

==Personal==
Long-Droppert is from [[Claremont, Western Australia]].<ref name=source2>{{cite news|title=Andrew picked for world event|newspaper=Wanneroo Times|location=Perth, Australia|date=May 15, 2007|page=71|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ZNAO&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11924072C6C12428&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9|accessdate=25 March 2012}}</ref>
<ref name=softball-aus-site/><ref name=claremont>{{cite news|accessdate=7 March 2012|title=Verity proves her mettle|newspaper=Western Suburbs Weekly|location=Perth, Australia|date=May 8, 2007|page=79|id=CWS_T-20070508-079-179064|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ZNAN&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=12247174E104E180&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref> She played teeball as a youngster.<ref name="claremont" /> In 2004, a letter by her was published in the letters section of the ''[[The Australian]]'' in support of gay marriage.<ref name=supports-gay-marriage>{{cite news|accessdate=12 March 2012|title=Letters to the Editor|newspaper=The Australian|location=Australia|date=May 7, 2004|author=MATP|page=14|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:AUSB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=1026A27B84AF48D5&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref> She attended the [[University of Western Australia]] and was in her second year in 2007.<ref name="claremont" />  She majored in arts/law.<ref name="claremont" />

==Softball==
Long-Droppert started playing softball when she was twelve years old,<ref name="claremont" /> and plays third base and outfield.<ref name="claremont"/> In 2007 and 2009, she had a scholarship with and played for the [[Australian Institute of Sport]] team.<ref name=ais-team>{{cite news|accessdate=7 March 2012|title=Weaver out on high note|newspaper=The Northern Times|location=Brisbane|date=February 27, 2009|first=Andre|last=Grimaux|page=64|id=TNT_T-20090227-1-064-931013|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:QGCBQ&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=126ADFC84D3A46B8&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref><Ref name=more-jr-2007>{{cite news|accessdate=7 March 2012|title=August games in sight|newspaper=Eastern Reporter|location=Perth, Australia|date=May 15, 2007|page=71|id=CES_T-20070515-071-171038|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ZNAC&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11924071826EBDE0&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref><ref name="claremont"/>  She has also had a softball scholarship with and played for the  [[Western Australian Institute of Sport]] in 2007.<ref name=source2>{{cite news|title=Andrew picked for world event|newspaper=Wanneroo Times|location=Perth, Australia|date=May 15, 2007|page=71|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ZNAO&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11924072C6C12428&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9|accessdate=25 March 2012}}</ref>
<Ref name=more-jr-2007>{{cite news|accessdate=7 March 2012|title=August games in sight|newspaper=Eastern Reporter|location=Perth, Australia|date=May 15, 2007|page=71|id=CES_T-20070515-071-171038|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ZNAC&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11924071826EBDE0&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref><ref name="claremont"/> She plays club softball for the [[Stirling Centrals]].<ref name="claremont"/>   She has represented [[Western Australia]] in national competions, first making the junior state team when she was fifteen.<ref name="claremont" />
===Junior national team===
Long-Droppert has been a member of Australia's junior national team.  She represented Australia at the 2007 Junior World Championships in the Netherlands.<ref name="claremont" /><ref name="more-jr-2007" /><ref name=third-source-lucky>{{Cite news|accessdate=7 March 2012|title=Games berth|newspaper=Melville Times|location=Perth, Australia|date=May 15, 2007|page=59|id=CMF_T-20070515-059-159038|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ZNAH&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11924071F00B60A0&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref><ref name=cite-4-for-gng>{{Cite news|accessdate=7 March 2012|title=Michelle in again|newspaper=Stirling Times|location=Perth, Australia|date=May 15, 2007|page=55|id=CST_T-20070515-055-155006|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ZNAL&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=119240726E7693B8&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref> Her team took home a bronze medal. In the semi-final loss to Japan, she was the only player to score a run by crossing home plate.<ref name=bronze-good>{{cite news|accessdate=12 March 2012|title=Dominic continues|newspaper=South East Advertiser|location=Brisbane, Australia|date=July 4, 2007|page=87|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:QGCBM&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11A31E943785E9B8&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref> In 2007, as a member of the U19 national team, she also participated in a softball tour of the Netherlands.<Ref name=u19-tour>{{Cite web|accessdate=7 March 2012|title=Andrew picked for world event|newspaper=Wanneroo Times|location=Perth, Australia|date=May 15, 2007|page=71|id=CWT_T-20070515-071-171058|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ZNAO&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11924072C6C12428&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref>

===Senior national team===
{{Wikinews|Japan beats Aussie Spirit in first two games of series}}
Long-Droppert has represented Australia as a member of the [[Australia women's national softball team]].<Ref name=another-loss>{{cite news|accessdate=7 March 2012|title=Arioto's triple lifts US past Australia 5-2|newspaper=Associated Press Archive|date=July 23, 2011|first=Jeff|last=Latzke|publisher=Associated Press|id=D9OL43D80|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:APAB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=138FA370CC3BF540&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref><ref name=2011-comment>{{cite news|accessdate=12 March 2012|title=BRIEFS|newspaper=The Sunday Age|location=Melbourne, Australia|date=July 24, 2011|page=18|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ASAB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=138AF8E779BB57B8&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref> In 2007, she represented Australia at the [[World University Games]].  It was her second time representing Australia at this event.<ref name="claremont"/><ref name=source2>{{cite news|title=Andrew picked for world event|newspaper=Wanneroo Times|location=Perth, Australia|date=May 15, 2007|page=71|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ZNAO&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11924072C6C12428&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9|accessdate=25 March 2012}}</ref> In March 2009, she participated in a Brisbane based training camp. <ref name=ais-team/> In 2011, she was a member of the Australian side that competed at the [[World Cup of Softball]]. She played in game at the Cup against the United States where Australia lost 5-2. It was her second loss on the day, also having played in a game where Australia lost to Japan. In the loss, she missed a diving catch, which allowed two runs to score for the opposition.<Ref name=another-loss>{{cite news|accessdate=7 March 2012|title=Arioto's triple lifts US past Australia 5-2|newspaper=Associated Press Archive|date=July 23, 2011|first=Jeff|last=Latzke|publisher=Associated Press|id=D9OL43D80|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:APAB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=138FA370CC3BF540&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref><ref name=2011-comment>{{cite news|accessdate=12 March 2012|title=BRIEFS|newspaper=The Sunday Age|location=Melbourne, Australia|date=July 24, 2011|page=18|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:ASAB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=138AF8E779BB57B8&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref> She is a member of the 2012 [[Australia women's national softball team]] and is trying to earn a spot to compete at the 2012 ISF XIII Women's World Championships .<ref name=softball-aus-site>{{cite web|accessdate=6 March 2012|publisher=Softball Australia|location=Australia|date=24 February 2012|title=Australian Open Women's Squad 2012|url=http://www.softball.org.au/extra.asp?ID=22086}}</ref>

===Professional team===
Long-Droppert played professionally for Baseball Softball Club Legnano of the Italian Softball League in 2010 and 2011.<ref name=softball-taly>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsclegnano.eu/squadra_2010.html|title=Baseball Softball Club Legnano 2010 Roster|accessdate=11 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=softball-taly2>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsclegnano.eu/squadra_2011.html|title=Baseball Softball Club Legnano 2011 Roster|accessdate=11 March 2012}}</ref>

